				<td colspan="2"><span>It is hard to tell, but, I always click it on as I am running abck to camp. 5%, 1%, I will take anything I can get when a tank is slow to pickup agro in Proving Grounds. I have been quadded for 4k in about 2 seconds before, and... ow. I usually dodge 4 out 5 or so. But, yesterday I took all 4, and an extra one. I did have Vesagran up, took 4 for 1011, instaneously. I say instanteously because I took stun on first hit, and my song ends message was after the 4th hit. 100% to 50% or so in one round is a bit scary.
<br />

<br />
Wind does scale it to 30 all stats with the flute from the Saryrn Event. Torment? Anyway, I have yet to tell if it makes a difference. 5% is too small to see in hits, but it shows up in mana efficiency over time for clerics. That is what the clerics I grouped with the last few days told me. Appears to be useless on raids, but does seem to have a benefit in long term (3+hour) grinds. Elemental and below grinds I would not even bother with it due to the timing on it. It really is just a pain in the wrist.
<br />

