				<td colspan="2"><span>The spell part is hard to test, since you dont know what was resisted vs. what was mitigated.  Here is how I tested this:  I had a cleric heal me while I fought a RS mob on Fire side.  If my wind mod (2.8 from puretone) affected the percent of the song, then it should have faded right away, as I would only need to take about 3k total damage to eat a 15% Vie for 450 max.  My rune didn't drop before it faded any time during the testing.  
<br />

<br />
My alternate test for this was Quarm; known 3k DD.  I have 5% Spell Shield, and with VoV and no resist song up to test this, I took a 2700 AE.  So I can say pretty conclusively that the percent mitigated is not affected by mod in any way.  
<br />

<br />
I have not yet deduced a good way to test whether or not the maximum amount absorbed is afected by mod or not.  At 5% mitigation, I need to take 9K damage in 18 secs, which is hard to coordinate, with only 10.8K hp buffed.  I suppose with a lot of effort, you could have a few clerics with Darby or something that could heal without taking the mob off of me to let the test run.  Other than that, we have a practical problem of being dead or losing agro before we can test the total damage.  
<br />
