				<td colspan="2"><span>In regards to the Rallos parse:
<br />
Well your mitigation numbers would be accurate if it were possible to pulse the song.  Using the parse's DPS numbers (1757), VoV would be eaten up in ~5.1sec.  Since there's a 15sec. recast plus a 3sec. cast time the actual mitigation numbers would be closer to 12150 damage absorbed over the entire 8min 3sec fight.  Pretty unimpressive.
<br />

<br />
Even if it were able to be chain casted, that would be the only song we would sing, thus giving up an ~159 point DS that'd crank out ~273 dps.
<br />

<br />
If it could be twisted, basically a 450 dmg rune every 9secs instead of 18sec, we could keep our ~273dps DS plus still absord ~24300 damage with VoV.  I suppose this is an acceptible compromise.
<br />

<br />
All around I feel this song is lacking.  The re-cast timer is too long, the percent absorbed is quite low (although the least likely thing to change), and the total damage absorbed is increadibly low; anything cranking out in minimum 500 to 750dps (this value has a range becuase song duration is variable) will eat up the rune before its full duration is up.
<br />

<br />
Just another take on these numbers.  I wish to see this song bolstered as it is quite a neat idea of a song, and quite frankly the only original song with Omens and I'd love to see it worth memming.</span></td>
