				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Verse of Vesagran <a name="68871"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 3 04 1:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I did some tests last night with a cleric and I'm convinced that an instrument does not raise the mitigation percentage.  However, I was not able to test if the instrument raised the 450 HP max. 
<br />

<br />
For the test I removed all my items so I had 25 on all resists.  Then the cleirc nuked me several times.  Each time the damage was the same.  Then I played this song and he nuked me several more times.  The damage taken was almost exactly 5% less, which makes sense.  Then I equipped an instrument and sang it.  Again the damage taken was 5% less. 
<br />

<br />
However, if the instrument does raise the 450 HP max then it might make this song usefull.  For instance, with epic 1.0 and IM3 you have a 2.6 mod.  450 * 2.6 = 1170.  Since you can only play this song about once every 18 seconds this would mean its max mitigation of 65 HP per second.
<br />

<br />
But in order to do 1170 of mitigated damage the group or tank would need to take 23,400 damage total over 18 seconds.  Most groups would not encounter this, but raids might.
<br />

<br />
So it seems to me that this song is only usefull against mobs that have very high DPS, and if, and only if, the mod raises the max HP.
<br />

<br />
If the mob does very high DPS and if the mod raises max HP then this song would be more useful than Nivs Melody of Preservation.
<br />

<br />
Dumaine
