				<td colspan="2"><span>I just noticed something else about Vesagran I'm not clear on...
<br />

<br />
The description here at EQdiva says it mitigates 5% melee damage (up to 450 HP), *and* 5% spell damage (up to 450 HP).  
<br />

<br />
Do these add together to reach 900 HP?  If so, mitagating 900 HP every 18 seconds is looking better.  That would work out to 50 HP per sec.  This is better than Niv's with a 2.6 mod. 
<br />

<br />
This makes many assumptions though.  The mob or mobs would need to do about 9000 melee and 9000 magic damage to mitigate 900 HP.
<br />

<br />
One use for this would be mobs that proc nasty AoEs frequently.  This would help mitagate 5% of the AoE for the group and then 5% of the tanks melee damage.
<br />

<br />
Dumaine</span></td>
